						               													<description>A mysterious roll and write, print and play game. Explore the mines, find treasures and discover the secret that lies beneath the surface.&amp;#10;Choose your favorite miner, gather resources, craft objects and get out of the mines in time... but beware! Dynamite is extremely dangerous and unstable.&amp;#10;The game includes:&amp;#10;Single player campaign&amp;#10;Multiplayer co-op&amp;#10;PVP&amp;#10;Paper clicker game mode&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Single Player quick rules&amp;#10;GAME SETUP&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Choose the mission you want to play. It&amp;rsquo;s better to play them in order;&amp;#10;     Pick the game map related to the mission you chose;&amp;#10;     Choose your character wisely (the starting object may be crucial);&amp;#10;     Choose the entrance where you want to begin your adventure. Analyze carefully&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;the tasks that you must accomplish in order to complete the mission, it&amp;rsquo;s important to pick the best spot to start;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The first turn begins. You have 16 turns to complete your mission and escape the mines. On the 17th turn, you lose the game. Don&amp;rsquo;t forget to mark the current spot in the progression bar placed at the bottom of the map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;TURN STRUCTURE&amp;#10;Movement: first, roll dice to determine the number of spots you can move. You can move in any direction, up to the number you obtained. If you roll 2 dice, you must choose one of the two results. You can use the other result to craft an object.&amp;#10;Action: once you&amp;rsquo;ve moved to the desired spot, check your Character Card to see the number of dice you can roll to perform actions. Both &amp;ldquo;Gathering&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Extracting&amp;rdquo; have their own specific value that you must obtain to perform that specific action. You can use one or more dice to craft objects.&amp;#10;End of turn: once you&amp;rsquo;ve completed all your actions, mark the current spot of the progress bar at the bottom of the board. When you are in a &amp;ldquo;dynamite&amp;rdquo; spot, throw dice to determine where the explosion will block your way.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
